beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: it def could be compared to woodchuck, but i felt that this was much better....my buddy picked up a 6er of alot of leinenkugels products in kansas...up until then id only had sunset wheat...this was a great beer i thought...but that only bad thing is that it didnt taste like beer...great to drink with a warm bowl of chili iin the winter or fall

I am a huge fan of this beer, it was a very light ale with a wonderful taste, it poured a light yellow, and had a small creamy head, tastes very light but still flavorful, this beer is perfect for spring time
i had high hopes for this beer but they were shot down .......teribleafter tase....sort of smels like pine........very bitter....my least favorite pale ale

as far as the rating......im not gonna give it credit.....but im to much of a red neck to fully knowck this beer......it has gotten me thru a lot of hard times...a allowed me to meet some interesting people

I defineitly did not enjoy this from a can, i dont know what it was but it was just to watery, i went to the world market in chattanooga to make my own six pack and i saw a bottle of this so i threw it in, i enjoyed it much more frmo the bottle, kind of a bitter almost vinegary taste in my opinion, but it leaves a nice after taste and is fairly drinkable

Poured golden brwon with a thick off white head, very flavorful, not to overwhelming with the strawberries. I def. agree with AskForJenny its a good beer for the old lady. Kind of leaves a thick taste in your mouth, but its a good taste so its all good. i love this beer
i really enjoyed this, very nice aroma, almost a hint of chocolate, maybe thats just me, i probably wont purchase it reguarlly but ill def. never turn it down.

i really enjoyed this beer, i got it out of there holiday pack, it poured a nice fruity taste, did have sort of an unpleasnt after taste...very good for cooking though....i cook my dear meat in beer and so far this gives it the best flavor
not really much to say here.....just another redneck cheap beer (i am a redneck...not making fun...trust me ive had quite a few) it tastes likewater with a little sugar salt and carbonation
most def. my "go to" cheap beer, unlike natty and keystone...this beer at least has a taste...honestly not that bad if your just looking for pulling a drunk one night

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: i really enjoyed this beer, it was really refreshing, def. had  that blue moon taste i agree, but more explosive. I picked up a 6 pack of this after moving furniture for about 6 hours...talk about a refrshing beer. I would suggest this to anyone, it is a great after work type beer.

This is by far my favorite beer of all time, i would suggest this to anyone, regardless of there prefrence on beer styles, of course i am probably biased because witbier is my favorite style. It pours very cloudy with a nice white head. It almost has a lemon lime smell to it along with hint of lemon zest in the flavor, very drinkable beer with a wonderful after taste as well. One of the few beers ill drink with breakfast.

This beer is a must. i just recently tasted it on tap for the first time at The Sandbar in Athens Ga, ive always been a huge fan of it out of the bottle, so you can imagine my delight when sampling out of the tap. It has a very thick head and a some what cloudy appearance like most white beers. Very nice citrus taste. I definetly suggest putting a slice of orange in it. Great beer
This is one of those beers that just screams " drink me with a steak". It is wonderful at dinner, and unlike most fulll flavored beers at isnt to filling.
its a good beer to drink if you want to get hammered, thats about its only purpose, but thats not always a bad thing
